  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, TreeNode, CallableSBase, NamedSBase, NamedSBaseWithDerivedUnit, Quantity, SBase, SBaseWithDerivedUnit, SBaseWithUnit, UniqueNamedSBase, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport, Variable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Compartment, Parameter, Species

    public abstract class Symbol
extends QuantityWithUnit
implements Variable
    The base class for Compartment, Species, Parameter. A symbol is a Variable of the system that declares a unit and a value, i.e., neither its Unit or UnitDefinition, nor its value are derived. A Symbol defines both fields. Furthermore, a Symbol may vary through a simulation and can be accessed within the model through its identifier and name attributes.
